Now the issue is identified properly.

Your deployment itself is healthy now:

odf-operator-controller-manager → 1/1 Available

pod is Running

deployment condition is healthy


But the operator keeps reconciling with this error:

InstallPlan not found for CSV odf-dependencies.v4.19.12-rhodf

This happened because you manually deleted:

oc delete csv odf-dependencies.v4.18.17-rhodf

OLM upgraded odf-operator to 4.19.12, but the dependent CSVs (odf-dependencies, rook-ceph, ocs-operator, etc.) never upgraded to 4.19.12.

So now you have a mixed state:

Component	Version

odf-operator	4.19.12
all other ODF operators	4.18.17


That mismatch is what is causing continuous reconciliation errors.

The fix is to force OLM to regenerate missing InstallPlans for all dependent operators.

Run these commands carefully.

First check whether catalog has 4.19 bundles:

oc get packagemanifest -n openshift-marketplace | grep -i odf

Then delete the stale subscriptions so OLM recreates proper dependency graph:

oc delete subscription odf-dependencies -n openshift-storage

Wait 20 seconds.

Then recreate it:

cat <<EOF | oc apply -f -
apiVersion: operators.coreos.com/v1alpha1
kind: Subscription
metadata:
  name: odf-dependencies
  namespace: openshift-storage
spec:
  channel: stable-4.19
  name: odf-dependencies
  source: redhat-operator-index
  sourceNamespace: openshift-marketplace
EOF

Then monitor:

watch -n 5 'oc get csv -n openshift-storage'

You should start seeing:

odf-dependencies.v4.19.12-rhodf

rook-ceph-operator.v4.19.12-rhodf

ocs-operator.v4.19.12-rhodf

mcg-operator.v4.19.12-rhodf

etc.


Once all move to 4.19.12:

reconciliation errors stop

CSV becomes Succeeded

ODF stabilizes completely


Do NOT delete the StorageCluster or Ceph resources. Your data plane is healthy. This is only an OLM/operator version skew issue.
